subSubSection.paragraph:
Bionomics
(
Figs 18–21
). Host plant is unknown (unidentified). Larvae mine in leaves in August and, judging from observed old (empty) leaf mines, in July. Larva pale yellowish green, with brownish green intestine and pale brown head (
Fig. 18
). The leaf mine is linear, as a slender gallery, contorted in the beginning, further on sinuous, with a thin central line of black frass (
Figs 19–21
). Adults occur in August–September.
